You assume the form of a creature of the same type as your normal form. The new form must be within one size category of your normal size. You can change into a member of your own kind or even into yourself. 

If the new form is capable of speech, you can communicate normally. You retain any spellcasting ability you had in your original form, but the new form must be able to speak intelligibly (that is, speak a language) to use verbal components and must have limbs capable of fine manipulation to use somatic or material components. 

You can freely designate the new form's minor physical qualities (such as hair color, hair texture, and skin color) within the normal ranges for a creature of that kind. The new form's significant physical qualities (such as height, weight, and gender) are also under your control, but they must fall within the norms for the new form's kind. You are effectively disguised as an average member of the new form's race.

OOC Information:

Using it once will transform you into the defined form, using it again will transform you back into the original form.

The widget works off alot of variables which are set with ##SetVarInt
alter_skin # (Changes skin colors only)
alter_hair # (Changes hair colors only)
alter_tattoo1 # (Changes tattoo1 color only)
alter_tattoo2 # (Changes tattoo2 color only)
alter_wings # (Changes wings model)
alter_tail # (Changes tail model)
alter_head # (Changes head model)
alter_model # (Changes the skin/model of the PC, only use dynamic 0-6)

##SetVarString alter_portrait X (Changes portrait, e.g. f_elf_01)

You can also set the scale of the desired form! 
##SetVarFloat pc_scale 1.0 (this is for the size of the player, this should automaticly be set by usage)
##SetVarFloat cr_scale 1.0 (sets the size of the new form)

changing the numbers to whatever scale they're supposed to be! 1.0 is default. every +/- 0.01 is 1% The usual range is 0.9 to 1.1, so just ask them what they want.

This tool enables a DM to copy and paste a group of placeables or a singulare plc. Mind that it creates placeables from the palette, and it should therefore only be used on a group you created from the DM Chooser.

Function 1: 
-create a group of max 30 placeables-
* click in the center of the group
* give the widget to a PC as a DC item
* the PC can use it to spawn the group now

Function 2:
-create copy of a sinle plc-
* Set the variable: " ##SetVarInt plcs_allowed x "where x is the number of times the pc can spawn the plc max.
* click on/near the desired plc
* give the widget to a PC as a DC item
* the PC can use it to spawn the plc as often as the set variable allows.
* as player use on yourself to despawn all spawned plcs fromthis widget

If you  make an error you can clean the widget by clicking on yourself. This only works if you are a DM. Upon selecting a group of PLCs the name of the widget changes to show it's been set.

NOTE: this item works from your DM avatar AS LONG AS YOU DON'T LOGOUT!

This is a widget to add up to three permanent visuals to the PC upon use. It also has the functionality to up to three instant visuals on use.

Note: a basic understanding of the debug mode commands would be handy to set up this tool.

Apply instant visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx1 x and then target the widget, where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx2 and pc_vfx3 being the values for visuals two and three.

Apply permanent visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx_dur1 x and then target the widget , where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx_dur2 and pc_vfx_dur3 being the values for visuals two and three.

Step 1: A DM stands next to the creature of your choice and uses this widget. The skin and the portrait of the creature are stored on the item.

Step 2: Make sure you are not polymorphed or using an alternate appearance.

Step 3: The DM gives you the item, which you use once to store your skin and portrait on the widget. Your character will be saved. 

From now on you can use the Skin Changer to... *drumroll* ...change your skin and portrait.

There are now extra features (these must be done by the DM before handing the item to the player):

pc_vfx can be applied as an integer to the skin widget to change the polymorph visual when transforming. Apply this by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx x and then target the widget, where x is the number of the visual.

pc_sfx1 (up tp pc_sfx3) can be applied to the skin widget as a string to add a sound effect when transforming. Apply this by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_sfx1 x and then target the widget, where x is the number of the sound.

A delay can be applied to the widget so it takes x amount of seconds before the target changes. Apply this by using the console command dm_setvarfloat delay 6.0 and then target the widget. This would add a delay of 6.0 seconds.
